casebody.data:
Borne, Respondent, v. Minicus, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. January 4, 1892.) Appeal from fourth district court. Action by John Borne against Louis Minicus.

Argued before Bookstaver, Bischoff, and Pryor, JJ.

W. R. Eeese, for appellant. W. F. Browne, for respondent.

No opinion. Judgment affirmed, with costs.
